Maui Highlights

  • Attend a luau

    Visit the Feast at Lele or the Kaanapali Beach Luau and celebrate your vacation Hawaiian style.

  • Mountaintop sunrises and sunsets

    Watch a sunset or sunrise from the peak of Haleakalā volcano, which translates as "house of the sun."

  • Hit the beach

    Lounge on the pearlescent sand of world-class beaches before cooling off in emerald waters. Kaanapali Beach is a must!

The average price per night for a 3-star hotel in Maui this weekend is $415, or $660 for a 4-star hotel. Looking for something even fancier? 5-star hotels in Maui this weekend cost around $846 per night (based on Booking.com prices).
On average, it costs $496 per night to book a 3-star hotel in Maui for tonight. You'll pay around $622 on average if you stay at a 4-star hotel tonight, while a 5-star hotel in Maui will cost around $990 (based on Booking.com prices).
Many families visiting Maui loved staying at Hotel Wailea, Relais & Châteaux - Adults Only, The Whaler Resort, and Residence Inn by Marriott Maui Wailea. Maui Kai 507, Hampton Inn & Suites Maui North Shore, and Maui Coast Hotel are also popular among family travelers.
Some of the best hotels in Maui near Front Street Lahaina include Hyatt Regency Maui Resort & Spa, Kaanapali Alii, and The Westin Maui Resort & Spa, Ka'anapali.

Hotels in Maui that offer a highly-rated breakfast include Courtyard by Marriott Maui Kahului Airport, Kohea Kai Hotel Maui, and Paia Inn.
Couples traveling to Maui loved staying at Hale Li'ili'i at Keawakapu #201, The Whaler Resort, and Hotel Wailea, Relais & Châteaux - Adults Only. These hotels in Maui are also highly rated by couples: Maui Kai 507, The Mauian Hotel, and The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas, Ka'anapali.

    The area is beautiful; however, the tragedy of the loss of...

    The area is beautiful; however, the tragedy of the loss of the Old Town Lahaina casts a pall over the area. If you have memories of before the fire, it is very, very sad to see the remains of buildings and know that over 100 people lost their lives. The sentiment of Lahaina Strong is wonderful and uplifting but as you speak with residents, the current, somber message is that we will never regain what has been lost and there is no definitive plan or timeline for rebuilding. You are asked to not take photos and to respect the area. There is a bypass road that has been built.

  • 8.0

    The hotel is very nice, it has a central pool overlooking...

    The hotel is very nice, it has a central pool overlooking the sea. The rooms are spacious and clean, offering coffee, tea, beach towels, personal care products (soap, shampoo, conditioner, body lotion). There is a restaurant right next to it, serving good local dishes, where you get 10% off your bill as hotel guests. There is a parking lot in front of the hotel entrance, for $10/day (+taxes). The staff is very nice and keen to accommodate your requests. We were there on our honeymoon and they set up the room very nicely. The location is very close to the airport, yet is a very curated hotel. Overall a bit expensive, but aligned to the high prices of Maui.
    A

  • 8.0

    Wailuku, especially staying in Maalaea is so central to all...

    Wailuku, especially staying in Maalaea is so central to all of Maui. It sits almost on the intersection of each of main roads of the island, 10 mins into down town Wailuku, 10 mins to Kihei, 10 mins to the airport, 20 mins to Paia, or Lahaina, or Wailea. Everywhere is close while Wailuku has much to offer by itself. The pub in Maalaea is great for casual dining while taking in a high position view over the marina, the ocean and Haleakala. The Mill (5mins away) has a wonderful restaurant, fantastic menu and very relaxing location. This is a favorite of ours.
    P

    And finally, a review
